Aruna Quadri yesterday claimed the men’s singles title at the ITTF Nigeria Open Challenge Plus by defeating Austria’s Gardos Robert 4-2. The victory gave Quadri the trophy and the $7,000 top prize money. At the competition held at the Molade Okoya Hall of the Teslim Stadium, Surulere in Lagos, an injured Quadri held on to win the six-game thriller 15-13, 11-3, 8-11, 11-6, 10-12, 11-1.
 
In the women’s singles game, Russia’s Mikhailova Polina went head to head in an exciting 4-3 come back to beat her compatriot, Noskova Yana.  “For now, I have to take care of my health because I have been representing Nigeria for the past 11 days. “Without taking treatment, I don’t know if I would be able to go to the Africa Games.” In the men’s double event, Nuytinck Cedric and Robinot Quentin defeated Nigeria’s duo of Toriola Segun and Omotayo Olajide 3-0 (11-7, 11-9, 12-10), while Russian duo of Mikhailova Polina and Noskova Yana won the women’s doubles event by beating Croatian duo of Jazbec Ida and Malobabic Ivana 3-2 (8-11, 5-11, 11-9, 13-11, 7-11). To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .